WEBVTT

00:15:29.556 --> 00:15:31.270
or they get extremely defensive.

00:15:31.294 --> 00:15:35.845
SD: It is remarkable to me that
as customized as our culture has gotten

00:15:35.869 --> 00:15:38.252
in matching different things --

00:15:38.276 --> 00:15:40.283
so, consumer preferences,

00:15:40.307 --> 00:15:42.502
you can act on them really specifically.

00:15:42.526 --> 00:15:46.543
Like, to have a digitally
searchable universe

00:15:46.567 --> 00:15:48.978
of things that you need to acquire

00:15:49.002 --> 00:15:53.331
is a massively efficient upgrade
over the way it used to be.

00:15:53.355 --> 00:15:55.848
I used to need
a Sears catalog or whatever,

00:15:55.872 --> 00:15:59.791
and now, whatever I want,
I can literally type it and find it.

00:15:59.815 --> 00:16:03.752
And so I feel like
our mechanisms right now